<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870915-0109 </DOCNO><HL> American Oil Raises a Stake</HL><DD> 09/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AOGTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Oil andamp; Gas Corp. said it increased its stake in WellTech Inc. to more than 80% from 37% by acquiring an additional 43% of the company in a stock swap.    American Oil andamp; Gas said WellTech holders received 1.7 shares of American Oil common for each WellTech share held. Additionally, the company said it is offering, also through a stock swap, to acquire the remaining 19% of closely held WellTech.    Houston-based WellTech provides completion, repair and work-over services for newly drilled and producing oil and gas wells. American Oil andamp; Gas operates an intrastate gas pipeline system. In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange yesterday, American Oil andamp; Gas closed at $9.25, up 87.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>